message.message_body: Just arrived at Grand Central
Cool, I'll meet you at the library in like 20 minutes
I am done with Justin Bieber
Wow, the library is huge!
Outside the New York Public Library
I'm going to be in your area this evening, want to meet for dinner?
Sure, we shouldn't be too late
Want to eat at the Chipotle across the street?
Sure, I've been craving a big ol' burrito
We'll meet you there at 6
I've seen dogs that weigh less than my burrito!
Got my tickets for the Dodgers game tomorrow. Would any of you want to meet up tomorrow afternoon?
Y
Definitely, where were you thinking of going?
Afraid I can't, Megan and I are in Pittsburgh.
Kim, Lizl, and I are going to be hanging out in LA tomorrow afternoon. Haven't picked a place yet, so suggest something.
How about Griffith Park?
I was just there for a talk.
I haven't been to Venice Beach in a while.
Big Mike approves
That sounds good to me
I'm in.
Def
Sure, I'll be there
Great, let's meet at the skate park.  I know none of us skates, but it's easy to find.
Great, let's meet at the skate park.  I know none of us skates, but it's easy to find.
I want in too.
I loooove California Fish Grill.  Good fish, good prices, and you get a lot of food.
Leaving my place now.  Should be there in 45 minutes or so
Finally found a parking spot.  Be there in a few
Paul, you making it today?
Ugh, just woke up with a terrible cold.  Can't do it.
Don't see things like this many other places
Yum
So nice here
Hi doggy!
To infinity, and Beyond!
Game's about to start.
That ball's out of here!
Well this game's gotten out of hand in a hurry.
Quake in your boots before the mighty Indians
Cleveland may not quake, but at least our rivers never caught on fire.
That's because they have no water to burn.
You're missing the point.
I'd rather have no water than water so polluted it can catch fire.
The Dodgers may have gotten thrashed, but I had a fun time.  Dodger dogs are the best.
Back home safe and sound.
